SIMPLE: impel
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Impel
<hw>Im*pel"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Impelled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Impelling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>impellere</ets>; pref. <ets>im-</ets> in + <ets>pellere</ets>,
<ets>pulsum</ets>, to drive. See <er>Pulse</er> a beat, and cf.
<er>Impulse</er>.]</ety> <def>To drive or urge forward or on; to press
on; to incite to action or motion in any way.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The surge <qex>impelled</qex> me on a craggy coast.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To instigate; incite; induce; influence; force;
drive; urge; actuate; move.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>impelled</ent>⟦br⟧
